cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.NE

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Speech and Dialogue Processing (cs.SD) as it deals with speech recognition systems. It could also belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL) as it involves natural language processing. The use of convolutional architectures suggests it could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Signal Processing (cs.SI). Finally, the modifications proposed in the paper to improve performance suggest it could also belong to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
